{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.48",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 48,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 48 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:1",
      "text": "Unto the end, a psalm for the sons of Core.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:2",
      "text": "Hear these things, all ye nations: give ear, all ye inhabitants of the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:3",
      "text": "All you that are earthborn, and you sons of men: both rich and poor together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:4",
      "text": "My mouth shall speak wisdom: and the meditation of my heart understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:5",
      "text": "I will incline my ear to a parable; I will open my proposition on the psaltery.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:6",
      "text": "Why shall I fear in the evil day? the iniquity of my heel shall encompass me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:7",
      "text": "They that trust in their own strength, and glory in the multitude of their riches,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:8",
      "text": "No brother can redeem, nor shall man redeem: he shall not give to God his ransom,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:9",
      "text": "Nor the price of the redemption of his soul: and shall labour for ever,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:10",
      "text": "And shall still live unto the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:11",
      "text": "He shall not see destruction, when he shall see the wise dying: the senseless and the fool shall perish together: And they shall leave their riches to strangers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:12",
      "text": "And their sepulchres shall be their houses for ever. Their dwelling places to all generations: they have called their lands by their names.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:13",
      "text": "And man when he was in honour did not understand; he is compared to senseless beasts, and is become like to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:14",
      "text": "This way of theirs is a stumblingblock to them: and afterwards they shall delight in their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:15",
      "text": "They are laid in hell like sheep: death shall feed upon them. And the just shall have dominion over them in the morning; and their help shall decay in hell from their glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:16",
      "text": "But God will redeem my soul from the hand of hell, when he shall receive me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:17",
      "text": "Be not thou afraid, when a man shall be made rich, and when the glory of his house shall be increased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:18",
      "text": "For when he shall die he shall take nothing away; nor shall his glory descend with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:19",
      "text": "For in his lifetime his soul will be blessed: and he will praise thee when thou shalt do well to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:20",
      "text": "He shall go in to the generations of his fathers: and he shall never see light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.48.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:21",
      "text": "Man when he was in honour did not understand: he hath been compared to senseless beasts, and made like to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
